    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>bacon lardons</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Once crispy, remove <strong>half</strong> the <strong>crispy</strong> <strong>bacon</strong> <strong>lardons</strong> and set them aside until later</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min (10-12 min for wholewheat)</p><p>Slice your <strong>sweet pea pods</strong> into thirds</p><p>Once the pasta has been cooking for 8 min, add the<strong> sliced sweet pea pods</strong> and cook for 2-3 min further or until the pasta is cooked with a slight bite and the sweet pea pods are tender</p><p>Once cooked, drain and reserve a cup of<strong> starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, trim, then finely slice your <strong>spring onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>tomato[es]</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>into wedges</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>chicken stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> sliced spring onion </strong>to the pan with the bacon and reduce the heat to medium, then cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> and <strong>soft cheese</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until starting to thicken</p><p>Season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> creamy sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip your <strong>mint leaves </strong>from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Add the <strong>salad</strong> and <strong>tomato wedges</strong> to a bowl with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong> and mix everything together \u2013 this is your <strong>leafy tomato salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Stir the <strong>cooked pasta & sweet pea pods</strong>,<strong> reserved crispy</strong> <strong>bacon</strong> <strong>slices </strong>and <strong>half</strong> your<strong> grated Italian hard cheese</strong> (save the rest for later!) through the<strong> </strong>creamy sauce<strong> </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy bacon & sweet pea pods pasta</strong></p><p>Tip: If the sauce is looking a little dry add a splash of the starchy pasta water</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-bacon-and-sweet-pea-pods-farfalle-with-leafy-tomato-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy bacon & sweet pea pods pasta </strong>with the<strong> leafy tomato salad </strong>to the side</p><p>Sprinkle over the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong> and garnish with the <strong>chopped mint</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
